This paper discusses incorporating modularity into Answer Set Programming, which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions Lifschitz and Turner's splitting set theorem for normal logic programs, which falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses program modules and their composition, which is a topic in Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper mentions stable model semantics, which is a concept in Description Logic (cs.DL).
